                "",
                "#doi:10.1080/00223131.2025.2457589"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "FACILITY": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "facility": [
                  "REAC"
                ],
                "institute": "2JPNKTO"
              },
              "free_text": [
                "",
                "Kyoto University Research Reactor (KUR) ."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "incident_source": [
                  "REAC"
                ],
                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                "The graphite thermal column (TC-Pn) in KUR.",
                "The nominal neutron flux intensity of TC-Pn is",
                "5.86E+10 (n/cm2/sec) at 1 MW power operation.",
                "The AUTHORs confirmed that the TC-Pn was well",
                "thermalized in the previous experiment.",
                "See Fig. 9 in J,NST,58,1061,2021 (REL-REF) ."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "ACTIV",
                "GSPEC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Based on Westcott convention method.",
                "Samples and monitors were irradiated in the TC-Pn",
                "for 1 hour under 1-MW power operation.",
                "The decay gamma-rays were measured with a germanium",
                "detector."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "HPGE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " High purity germanium detector, relative",
                "efficiency of 25%.",
                "The gamma-ray peak efficiencies of the Ge detector",
                "were measured using a Eu-152 source and a mixed source",
                "AM-8140 (Am-241, Cd-109, Co-57, Ce-139, Hg-203,",
                "Sn-113, Cs-137, Co-60 and Y-88) .",
                "The uncertainty in the source radioactivity was 1.5%",
                "for both of the standard sources."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The reaction rates of the target reactions were",
                "obtained from the yields of the gamma rays emitted",
                "from the irradiated samples.",
                "The thermal-neutron fluxes were derived using neutron",
                "flux monitors: Au-197 and Co-59.",
                "- For the Er sample: (5.326+-0.086)E+10 (n/cm2/sec)",
                "- For the Hf sample: (5.411+-0.087)E+10 (n/cm2/sec)",
                "Because the neutron flux in the TC-Pn is well",
                "thermalized, epithermal component in Westcott",
                "convention method was negligibly small.",
                "The capture cross sections were derived using",
                "the reaction rates and the thermal-neutron fluxes.",
                "The thermal capture cross sections for monitors and",
                "the g-factors were taken from REL-REF."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "CORRECTION": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Self-shielding coefficients for thermal neutrons were",
                "calculated from neutron capture cross-sections and",
                "area densities of the sample and the monitors. The",
                "coincidence summing effect was estimated from the",
                "peak-to-total ratios and the peak efficiencies."
              ]
            }
          ],
